Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.56,0:00:04.73,sign_14_1_Do_I_smell____mi,Sign,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(691,1227)}Do I smell... miso soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.01,0:00:03.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Do I smell... miso soup?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.58,0:01:59.89,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,{OP}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.37,0:00:24.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Kyou,0000,0000,0000,,Good morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.42,0:00:30.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.22,0:02:02.38,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I wasn't told we were \Ngoing to be roommates!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:04.26,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,We don't have enough rooms, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.72,0:02:06.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.04,0:02:07.88,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,She agreed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.88,0:02:08.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Kyou,0000,0000,0000,,It was an order.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:09.94,0:02:11.76,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you get it, Atsushi-kun?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.45,0:02:14.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Get what?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.67,0:02:18.24,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Without any kin, \Nshe is as alone as can be.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.44,0:02:21.53,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Besides, the Port Mafia may \Nsend assassins after her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.53,0:02:22.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,That's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.17,0:02:24.61,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,You should protect her.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.79,0:02:27.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I'll do my best!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.40,0:02:31.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,If you have the time to mess with Atsushi,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.92,0:02:35.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,write up the report about your \Ncapture by the Port Mafia!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.39,0:02:37.20,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Atsushi-kun...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.20,0:02:38.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:38.22,0:02:40.55,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,Write the report for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.71,0:02:41.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.02,0:02:45.47,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be about the person who \Nplaced a bounty on your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.47,0:02:46.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You found out who?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.98,0:02:49.39,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,According to the Port Mafia's \Ncommunication records,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.53,0:02:51.68,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,the bounty was funded by \Nthe leader of The Guild,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:51.68,0:02:54.04,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,a North American organization of the gifted.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.19,0:02:56.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild is considered an urban legend.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.74,0:02:59.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Their agents are said to hold \Nkey positions in finance,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.70,0:03:01.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,politics, and the military.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.63,0:03:04.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,They are a secret society who \Nuse their limitless funds
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.23,0:03:06.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,and abilities to plot countless schemes.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.88,0:03:10.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Why would such a group want Atsushi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.05,0:03:16.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,You need to come see this!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.69,0:03:25.51,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we've been preempted.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.73,0:03:36.73,sign_5101_38_Episode_12___Bor,Sign 0335,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 12 \N Borne Back Ceaselessly into the Past
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.02,0:03:39.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I'm glad to finally meet you,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.10,0:03:40.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,President Fukuna...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.06,0:03:41.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Fukuda?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.29,0:03:43.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,Fukuzawa.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.29,0:03:44.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,That's right!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.61,0:03:48.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,By the way, was it a bad move to \Npark the chopper on the road?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.90,0:03:52.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,You have come a long way \Nfrom a foreign land.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.40,0:03:54.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,So, what do you wish to discuss?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.66,0:03:59.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Fran,0000,0000,0000,,Well, this is a rare design.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.11,0:04:02.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Fran,0000,0000,0000,,And I consider myself something \Nof an expert in porcelain.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.10,0:04:04.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Fran,0000,0000,0000,,What brand is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.16,0:04:06.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Fran,0000,0000,0000,,Royal Blanc?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.57,0:04:08.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Fran,0000,0000,0000,,Or is it perhaps El Zelga?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.30,0:04:10.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,It's from Shimomura China and \NCeramics, next door.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.40,0:04:12.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my apologies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.22,0:04:16.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Call me Francis, old sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.32,0:04:21.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I lead an organization called \NThe Guild in North America.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.33,0:04:23.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, I personally own
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.01,0:04:25.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,three conglomerates, five hotels,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.40,0:04:26.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,an airline, a railway company, and—
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.57,0:04:27.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Francis.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.39,0:04:31.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,I have received reports that \Nyou used a bounty
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.49,0:04:34.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,to encourage the Port Mafia to attack us.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.75,0:04:35.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,Is this true?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.07,0:04:38.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, that was my mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.89,0:04:41.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I had no idea that this country's \Ncriminal organization
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.55,0:04:43.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,would be so incompetent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.85,0:04:46.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,To make amends, I come bearing \Na profitable business deal.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.78,0:04:48.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,This company isn't so bad.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.52,0:04:50.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,The neighborhood is aesthetically \Npleasing, as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.67,0:04:51.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,So...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.43,0:04:55.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I'd like to buy this company.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.90,0:04:57.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Don't get me wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.77,0:04:59.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I am quite capable of \Nbuying all the properties
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.69,0:05:01.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,visible from here along with your company.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:04.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I have no interest in this \Nbuilding or your employees.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.21,0:05:06.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I am only interested in one thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.84,0:05:07.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,You don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.03,0:05:09.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.32,0:05:11.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Hand over your Gifted Business Permit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.44,0:05:17.53,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,For a group of gifted individuals \Nto legally open a business,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.67,0:05:19.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,they need a permit issued by the \NMinistry of Internal Affairs'
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.96,0:05:21.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,gifted special operations division.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.30,0:05:25.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Those blockheads are about the only \Nones you can't buy with money.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.37,0:05:30.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,After all, we are a secret society \Nwith no official existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.63,0:05:32.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,In order to keep peace with the Ministry
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.62,0:05:35.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,and do what we need to do to find \Nwhat we're looking for in this city,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:35.57,0:05:36.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,the permit is—
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.80,0:05:37.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,I refuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.45,0:05:40.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,What, this isn't enough?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.58,0:05:43.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll add this.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.06,0:05:45.63,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,It's a limited edition model,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.63,0:05:48.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,made to order with diamonds.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.32,0:05:50.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,Just as lives cannot be bought with money,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.50,0:05:53.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,nothing is worth giving up our permit.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.66,0:05:56.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,The permit is the beating \Nheart of this Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.78,0:05:58.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,It embodies the hope of \Nthe special ops division,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.47,0:06:01.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,as well as the spirit of Natsume-sensei,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.16,0:06:03.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,who worked tirelessly to \Nobtain us the permit.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.37,0:06:06.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,It is not meant to easily fall into \Nthe hands of the filthy rich,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:09.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,who have dollar bills for brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.40,0:06:11.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,So you're saying there are things \Nyou can't buy with money?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.29,0:06:14.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,That's the mantra of the poor.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.88,0:06:18.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Your bravado is pointless if all \Nof your employees disappear
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.85,0:06:20.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,and your agency ceases to function.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.59,0:06:23.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be too late to change your mind then.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.26,0:06:25.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,I'll take your advice to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.05,0:06:27.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Fuku,0000,0000,0000,,I suggest you leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.75,0:06:30.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.83,0:06:34.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Our visitors are leaving.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.11,0:06:35.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.21,0:06:36.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,I'll see you out!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.54,0:06:40.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I'll post a message \Nin the morning newspaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.83,0:06:43.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look at it, old sport.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.57,0:06:46.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,I always get what I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.73,0:06:52.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Nice hat.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.65,0:06:53.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.11,0:06:55.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Kenji,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.62,0:07:08.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:09.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Does it look good on me?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.54,0:07:12.26,Stray Dogs - Default,James,0000,0000,0000,,You'd look better in burlap.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.48,0:07:13.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What was that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.23,0:07:14.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Hmph.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.20,0:07:19.73,Stray Dogs - Default,Francis,0000,0000,0000,,First, there was one.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.77,0:07:24.96,sign_10616_123_The_Following__M,Sign 0723,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(255,1)}The Following \NMorning
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.21,0:07:24.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, did you see the morning news?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.19,0:07:26.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,It's on the TV, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.55,0:07:28.70,Stray Dogs - Top,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}Please see for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.34,0:07:32.95,Stray Dogs - Top,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}A seven-story building \Nhas vanished overnight.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.49,0:07:34.75,Stray Dogs - Top,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}According to one source,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.75,0:07:38.67,Stray Dogs - Top,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}the building housed a front \Ncompany for the Port Mafia.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.67,0:07:41.99,Stray Dogs - Top,TV,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}It was allegedly used as \Nan office by their agents.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.54,0:07:42.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the message...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.81,0:07:47.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Kenji-kun hasn't been back to \Nthe dorm since seeing them off.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.32,0:07:50.44,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,So they'll annihilate \Nanyone who opposes them,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.44,0:07:52.91,Stray Dogs - Default,D,0000,0000,0000,,be they the Port Mafia or the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.06,0:07:55.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Tanizaki, from now on, you're \Nprohibited from working alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.15,0:07:58.15,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Look for Kenji with Atsushi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.44,0:08:00.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai, you're with me!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.09,0:08:01.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,We need to meet with the president.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.63,0:08:03.67,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,We don't know what kind of \Ngifts they possess.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.80,0:08:05.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,If you make contact with the enemy,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.29,0:08:06.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Kuni,0000,0000,0000,,don't engage them. Run!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.79,0:08:07.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.59,0:08:11.30,sign_11691_143_Pedestrian__Supp,Sign 0807,0000,0000,0000,,Pedestrian \NSupport System
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.67,0:08:11.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi, you should go back to the Agency.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.66,0:08:12.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,It's too dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.94,0:08:14.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,They can make entire buildings disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.43,0:08:15.69,Stray Dogs - Top,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,{an8}Elise-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.80,0:08:16.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't matter where I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.84,0:08:19.27,Stray Dogs - Top,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,{an8}Please come out, hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.55,0:08:17.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Right, Atsushi-san?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.98,0:08:19.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,W-Well, sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.20,0:08:20.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Atsushi-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.10,0:08:21.68,Stray Dogs - Top,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,{an8}Elise-chan, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.36,0:08:23.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Unlike you, my sister isn't gifted!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.28,0:08:24.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,She'll hold us back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.48,0:08:25.10,Stray Dogs - Top,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,{an8}Elise-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.25,0:08:25.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,How dare you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.80,0:08:28.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,You said you'd do anything I said!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.81,0:08:27.12,Stray Dogs - Top,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,{an8}Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.76,0:08:31.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,That was yesterday when you were forcing me to—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.24,0:08:33.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.61,0:08:36.07,sign_11691_143_Pedestrian__Supp,Sign 0836,0000,0000,0000,,Pedestrian Support System
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.63,0:08:39.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, it's too dangerous, so go back!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.09,0:08:40.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, really?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.19,0:08:42.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Naomi,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd like, I can help \Nyou remember your pleasure—
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.88,0:08:45.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.30,0:08:48.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,N-No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.07,0:08:49.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:51.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.66,0:08:53.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you go, Naomi?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.52,0:08:54.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Is it an enemy attack?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.06,0:08:56.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:58.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,I didn't sense anything off.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.53,0:08:59.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.44,0:09:00.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful, Tanizaki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.88,0:09:02.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, Elise-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.95,0:09:05.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I'm in trouble now...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.60,0:09:07.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Give Naomi back!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.99,0:09:10.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Found you!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.59,0:09:14.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.34,0:09:18.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Let's play.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.82,0:09:28.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Welcome, everyone, to Anne's Chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.27,0:09:30.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this is embarrassing.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.67,0:09:33.37,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,So many people are looking right at me.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.55,0:09:36.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm not very good at talking to strangers.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.83,0:09:37.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But that won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.92,0:09:40.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I have to give a proper explanation, \Nor everyone will be so lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.71,0:09:44.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,After all, you were all brought \Nunawares to this strange place.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.91,0:09:47.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,If I were you, \Nmy heart would be pounding—
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.06,0:09:48.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Where's Naomi?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.29,0:09:50.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.89,0:09:52.74,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I should explain that first.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.08,0:09:54.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Your agents are over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:56.69,0:09:57.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Kenji-kun!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.75,0:09:58.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.43,0:10:01.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Damn it!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.20,0:10:01.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Naomi!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.97,0:10:03.64,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It won't open without the key.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.75,0:10:05.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,That one opens, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.88,0:10:09.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,They're all frozen.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.42,0:10:10.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Has time come to a stop?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.46,0:10:13.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,My name is Lucy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.23,0:10:17.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,This is a dimension \NI created with my ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.49,0:10:19.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But worry not.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.11,0:10:21.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You can leave whenever you want, \Nthrough that white door.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.17,0:10:25.13,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,That is, if you don't want \Nyour colleagues back.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.55,0:10:27.06,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,What do you want?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.06,0:10:28.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,That's easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.36,0:10:31.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I just want you to play \Nwith Anne in this chamber.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.92,0:10:33.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Come, Anne.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.19,0:10:42.12,Typewriter Text Sign,Sign 1039,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(543,57)}Guild Apprentice: \NLucy M
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.80,0:10:42.12,Typewriter Text Sign,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(99,75)}Ability: \NAnne of\N Abyssal Red
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.05,0:10:46.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Anne loves to play.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.31,0:10:48.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,She's a bit needy, but she's quite cute.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.19,0:10:55.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But if you leave through that door,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.18,0:10:57.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,you'll forget everything \Nthat happened in this room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.15,0:10:59.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Do you get it, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.08,0:11:03.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, my..
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.54,0:11:05.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Only three of you are left?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.41,0:11:06.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,It's not safe here.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.81,0:11:08.12,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You should run.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.17,0:11:10.92,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I'm looking for a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.22,0:11:13.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,She's lovely, just like an angel.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.32,0:11:15.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Have you see her?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.55,0:11:18.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,No, I'm sorry to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:18.90,0:11:19.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.59,0:11:22.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Her name is Elise-chan.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.50,0:11:25.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, ever since we've been separated,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.72,0:11:27.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I've been beside myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.10,0:11:31.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,She may be behind that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.29,0:11:33.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,If that's the case,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.68,0:11:35.70,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll regret running away \Nfor the rest of my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.21,0:11:37.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,So I'll stay, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.85,0:11:40.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.04,0:11:41.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,The rules are simple.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.84,0:11:44.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Play tag with my lovely Anne.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.35,0:11:46.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,If she tags you, you lose.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.23,0:11:51.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,If you can open the door using that key\N before she catches you, you win.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.46,0:11:53.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I'll return the hostages.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.36,0:11:54.71,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Well?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.71,0:11:56.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Who's in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.78,0:11:58.35,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Can two play at once?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.53,0:12:00.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.37,0:12:02.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It's more fun if we play all together.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.18,0:12:09.56,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,We can win if we use Tanizaki-san's \NLight Snow ability to project illusions.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.94,0:12:11.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you ready?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.58,0:12:12.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Tani,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.48,0:12:13.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Ready, set...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.15,0:12:17.22,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.90,0:12:19.87,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,She's fast!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.05,0:12:22.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Caught...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.93,0:12:26.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,{Eyecatch}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:25.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,the first one!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.76,0:12:29.47,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Tanizaki-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.76,0:12:36.21,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,We've made yet another friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.90,0:12:38.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What a great day, Anne.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.70,0:12:40.32,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What? What's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.32,0:12:41.56,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You want more?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.91,0:12:43.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.48,0:12:57.84,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Wow, amazing!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.08,0:12:59.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I want to see more.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.92,0:13:04.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What a strong, useful ability...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.52,0:13:07.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure you were valued highly \Nfrom the moment you were born.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.25,0:13:10.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I heard you're an orphan.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.83,0:13:13.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I grew up in an orphanage, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.20,0:13:15.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It was a very cold place.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.29,0:13:20.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,After using ice-cold rags \Nto clean the whole day,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.80,0:13:23.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,my fingers would ache for days.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.22,0:13:26.72,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Given my ability,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.77,0:13:29.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,everyone thought I was a freak.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.53,0:13:33.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I heard the Agency was desperate \Nto find you when you were taken.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.32,0:13:35.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,How wonderful.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.98,0:13:38.83,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It must be because you have a great ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.83,0:13:39.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.34,0:13:42.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,The Guild took me in because they \Nsaw potential in my ability, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:45.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But there is no room for error in The Guild.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.12,0:13:48.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,If I fail in this mission,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.39,0:13:50.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I will be tossed aside \Nlike a used napkin.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.86,0:13:53.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Then I'll be all alone again.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.25,0:13:55.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.74,0:13:58.29,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Why does it have to be you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.81,0:14:00.51,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Why can't it be me?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.16,0:14:02.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It's so unfair.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.15,0:14:06.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You should know how I feel, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.01,0:14:08.23,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You should stay in this room forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.05,0:14:13.90,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,The only way out is to put \Nthe key in that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.92,0:14:18.50,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.50,0:14:19.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I win!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.08,0:14:21.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Watch out, boy!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.50,0:14:21.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.18,0:14:30.01,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Be careful. The key is important.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.15,0:14:32.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I thought I'd win if I opened \Nthe door with the key!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.88,0:14:35.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,That's right. If you could open it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.77,0:14:40.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea how to use \Na key like this, myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.21,0:14:44.39,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,So there was no way to \Nwin in the first place.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.03,0:14:47.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,The real game starts now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.67,0:14:50.62,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You seem to be a genius at tag,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.39,0:14:54.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,but I wonder how long your \Nsoul will last like this?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.53,0:15:03.89,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way to counter this.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.20,0:15:05.75,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I'll be caught eventually.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.74,0:15:09.80,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I can't hope to turn the tide now.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.04,0:15:13.35,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I have no choice but to hope that \NDazai-san and the others will come!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.35,0:15:15.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,You're going to run away, \Nleaving your friends behind?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.35,0:15:16.36,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Even if he were in this situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:18.86,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Dazai-san'd think of something!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.55,0:15:21.37,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,But I can't!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:24.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,No, boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.08,0:15:26.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Your enemy lies that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.17,0:15:29.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I wouldn't advise running away \Nin this particular case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.36,0:15:32.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Er, that is,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:36.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,if you'd trust the words of your \Nlocal neighborhood physician.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.94,0:15:39.08,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,If you were to believe her words,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.08,0:15:42.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,you'll forget everything once \Nyou leave through that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.40,0:15:44.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You'll remember neither \Nthe enemy's subterfuge,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:44.58,0:15:46.10,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,nor your colleagues in danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.10,0:15:47.97,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,And the enemy will continue \Nto press her attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.41,0:15:49.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you something of use.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.67,0:15:52.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,In game theory,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.25,0:15:54.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,the optimal strategy is to launch
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.00,0:15:58.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,a total counteroffensive on an \Nenemy who has attacked you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.82,0:16:00.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Crush the enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.86,0:16:02.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,But how?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.48,0:16:04.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,An arrogant enemy who feels invincible
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.48,0:16:06.86,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,is the most vulnerable opponent of all.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.99,0:16:11.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,And did I hear right, that \Nthe ones beyond that door
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.72,0:16:14.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,are the very ones who desperately \Ntried to save you when you were taken?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.71,0:16:19.83,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.25,0:16:22.61,Stray Dogs - Italics,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,They all saved me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.07,0:16:24.79,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Are you done with the chit-chat?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.93,0:16:26.58,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Is your motivation back?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.18,0:16:29.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,It's my turn, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.14,0:16:30.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.12,0:16:33.19,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,That is your optimal solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.43,0:16:35.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It wouldn't be fun any other way.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.73,0:16:37.59,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.76,0:16:39.17,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,It's already over.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.55,0:16:42.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Another one!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.42,0:16:44.80,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Of course! There are two of you.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:45.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Shit!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.55,0:16:53.02,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,All right, that's that.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.31,0:16:56.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,So, what will you do, mister?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.66,0:16:58.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.44,0:17:00.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,the tiger didn't get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.96,0:17:04.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,So I could let you go as a \Nsign of my appreciation.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.67,0:17:09.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Or maybe I want to see your expression \Nwhen Anne catches you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.26,0:17:11.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to try me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.96,0:17:15.18,Stray Dogs - Italics,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What? What's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.11,0:17:17.73,Stray Dogs - Italics,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,My legs are trembling \Nso much, I can't move.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.64,0:17:21.09,Stray Dogs - Italics,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Is this pure malice?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.58,0:17:24.26,Stray Dogs - Italics,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But why can't Anne move, either?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.90,0:17:28.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,It won't work.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.62,0:17:31.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You've already lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.87,0:17:33.60,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.96,0:17:38.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.16,0:17:41.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,But I know I shut the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.84,0:17:42.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.08,0:17:45.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You've made one mistake.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.42,0:17:47.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,This fight was two against \None from the very start!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.82,0:17:50.57,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,The moment the door opened,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.78,0:17:54.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Tanizaki-san used his Light Snow \Nability to create a false door.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.53,0:17:55.69,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,Impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.92,0:17:58.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,And you were able to resist the force
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.43,0:18:00.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,sucking you into the room with \Nyour arms and legs alone?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.03,0:18:03.25,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You misunderstand me.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.79,0:18:06.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I am not strong, and I'm not popular.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.87,0:18:09.54,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Rather, I've led a cursed life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.90,0:18:13.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,That's why I understand your jealousy \Nand hatred of others all too well.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.18,0:18:17.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't really want you \Nto fail this mission!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.41,0:18:19.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want you to lose the place \Nwhere you can feel you belong!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.37,0:18:21.76,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,But because I'm weak and inexperienced,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:21.76,0:18:23.44,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I can think of no other way!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.44,0:18:24.16,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.58,0:18:27.75,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.98,0:18:30.26,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I tied a ribbon to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.42,0:18:38.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Release your ability and let everyone go!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.41,0:18:41.14,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Or I'll drag you into the room.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.88,0:18:44.11,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Without a key, the door won't open.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:46.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,That means if you're imprisoned inside,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.18,0:18:48.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,no one can ever open that door.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.14,0:18:51.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,If that happens, you won't \Nbe able to return to reality
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.61,0:18:53.85,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,even if you release your ability.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.36,0:18:55.43,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Am I wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.58,0:18:56.78,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,That's...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.78,0:18:59.33,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Our abilities aren't tools of convenience \Nmade to control everyone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.33,0:19:01.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I know that better than most.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.51,0:19:03.88,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want to be trapped in the dimension \Nof your own making until you die—
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.23,0:19:07.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,No, even after you die?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.49,0:19:10.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,I... I can't afford to fail!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.24,0:19:11.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,I'm going to let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:11.90,0:19:15.41,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You only have that split second \Nbefore the door closes to decide.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.41,0:19:17.27,Stray Dogs - Default,Lucy,0000,0000,0000,,No, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.25,0:19:43.82,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Um, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.16,0:19:45.03,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,If I...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.33,0:19:46.77,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,If I can do anything for you...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.49,0:19:49.24,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Um!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.25,0:19:53.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Elise-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.18,0:19:56.04,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.04,0:19:57.36,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Where've you been!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.36,0:19:59.20,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I was so worried!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.20,0:20:00.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You just up and vanished...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:00.96,0:20:04.98,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,I thought Rintarou would worry \Nif I suddenly disappeared.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.65,0:20:07.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to make Rintarou cry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.61,0:20:09.61,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,That's so mean, Elise-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.61,0:20:11.31,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,But I forgive you, because you're so cute!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.63,0:20:14.81,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouka-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.53,0:20:17.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,You came to get me?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.86,0:20:19.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Kyou,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.02,0:20:21.18,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.53,0:20:24.07,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,We'll be taking our leave now.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.44,0:20:29.46,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your advice earlier.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.35,0:20:32.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,So you're a doctor?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.63,0:20:34.09,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Ex-doctor.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.46,0:20:36.34,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, I'm just a middle-aged man
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.34,0:20:37.96,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,keeping a small group of people in line.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.20,0:20:39.99,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Boy...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.16,0:20:43.30,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,A logical, optimal solution exists \Nin any wartime situation,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.30,0:20:45.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how difficult the challenge.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.43,0:20:48.87,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,You must not forget that,\N especially in times of confusion
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.87,0:20:50.94,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,when you might feel \Ninclined to recklessness.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.59,0:20:52.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.71,0:20:53.65,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.96,0:20:58.40,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,There is a way, even in difficult times...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.50,0:21:03.49,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong, Kyouka-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.58,0:21:05.66,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouka-chan?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.40,0:21:07.45,Stray Dogs - Default,Naka,0000,0000,0000,,Kyouka-chan!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.99,0:21:11.90,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I had a good time.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:14.28,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I wanted to return to my younger days
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.28,0:21:17.91,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,and use my ability to mow down \Nmy enemies left and right.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.16,0:21:19.55,Stray Dogs - Default,Elise,0000,0000,0000,,You're too old for that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:21.05,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,That's so mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.74,0:21:23.52,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,I may not look like much, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.19,0:21:46.48,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,So this is a Guild assassin?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.66,0:21:47.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Chuuya,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.57,0:21:49.42,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,The Agency and The Guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.68,0:21:53.00,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,It seems we are in a challenging \Nwartime situation, ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.29,0:22:02.80,sign_31536_439_Port_Mafia_Leade,Sign 2156,0000,0000,0000,,Port Mafia Leader:  \NMori Ougai
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.74,0:21:57.95,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,We need an optimal solution.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.38,0:22:00.68,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,The Agency and The Guild...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.48,0:22:02.80,sign_31612_440_Ability___Vita_S,,0000,0000,0000,,Ability:\N Vita Sexualis
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.01,0:22:05.93,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,Those who oppose us will be crushed,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.45,0:22:07.39,Stray Dogs - Default,Ougai,0000,0000,0000,,and annihilated.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:08.51,0:22:09.93,sign_31853_445_To_Be_Continued,Sign 2209,0000,0000,0000,,To Be Continued
